Responsibilities:

Responsible for day-to-day operations support in data centre;
Incident handling, problem troubleshooting and escalation to upper tier;
Operate computer equipment;
Maintain log books and records;
Coordinate and support external customers as needed
Requirements:

Knowledge in Electrical / Mechanical / Fire Services / Building Services Engineering or related disciplines;
With minimum 2 years related experience;
Exposure in data centre will be an advantage;
Basic knowledge in PC skills;
Responsible, willing to learn and with positive attitude;
Good communication skills, customer-oriented;
12-hour shift / flexible working between 2 to 4 days a week
Candidate with no working experience will be considered as Trainee Technician; 
Fresh Graduates are also welcome
You have a career opportunity in gaining knowledge and experience in serving one of the largest Data Center providers for local and international enterprise.

Attractive remuneration package and fringe benefit will be offered to the right candidate. Interested parties, we appreciate if you must send your resume stating with cover letter, current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Administration Department by clicking Apply Now.

For more information, please visit our website at http://www.oneas1a.com
All information collected will be kept strictly confidential and for recruitment purpose only.
